        <updateDate>2021-01-15T14:24:11Z</updateDate>
        <text>
          <![CDATA[ <p>This joint resolution proposes a constitutional amendment limiting the pardon power of the President.</p> <p>The amendment prohibits the President from granting a pardon or reprieve to himself or herself, to family members or members of the administration, to paid campaign employees, to a person or entity for an offense motivated by an interest of any of those people, or to a person or entity for an offense directed by or coordinated with the President. </p> <p>The amendment also invalidates pardons issued for a corrupt purpose.</p>]]>
        </text>
      </summary>
